## {{ drug.molecular_formula }}

Sodium Starch Glycollate contains not less than 2.8 per cent and not more than 4.5 per cent of sodium, Na, calculated with reference to the material washed with Ethanol (95%) and dried as described under Assay.

Identification: A: The infra-red absorption spectrum,  after suitable expansion of the transmittance scale, is concordant with the reference spectrum of sodium starch glycollate or with the spectrum obtained from sodium starch glycollate RS.

B: To {{ drug.strength }} of a 2% w/v dispersion in water add 0.{{ drug.strength }} of 0.005M iodine; a dark blue colour is produced.

C: The {{ drug.dosage_form }} obtained in the test for Heavy metals gives the reactions of sodium salts,

pH: Between 5.5 and 7.5, determined in a 2.0% w/v dispersion in carbon dioxide-free water,.

Heavy metals: Not more than 20 ppm, determined by Method A,  on {{ drug.strength }} of a {{ drug.dosage_form }} prepared in the following manner. To 4.{{ drug.strength }} in a silica or platinum dish add {{ drug.strength }} of a 50% w/v {{ drug.dosage_form }} of sulphuric acid, heat in a water-bath and then cautiously over a flame at about 600o. Continue heating until all black particles have disappeared, allow to cool, add 0.{{ drug.strength }} of 1M sulphuric acid, heat to ignition once again and allow to cool. Add 0.{{ drug.strength }} of 2M ammonium carbonate, evaporate to dryness and cautiously ignite. To the residue add {{ drug.strength }} of hydrochloric acid, evaporate to dryness on a water-bath and dissolve the residue in {{ drug.strength }} of water.

Iron: {{ drug.strength }} of the {{ drug.dosage_form }} obtained in the test for Heavy metals complies with the limit test for iron, (20 ppm).

Sodium chloride: Not more than 10.0%, determined by the following method. To {{ drug.strength }} add 20.{{ drug.strength }} of 0.1M silver nitrate and {{ drug.strength }} of nitric acid and boil carefully for 30 minutes. Cool and add a sufficient volume of a saturated {{ drug.dosage_form }} of potassium permanganate to change the colour of the {{ drug.dosage_form }} to red. Discharge the colour by the dropwise addition of hydrogen peroxide {{ drug.dosage_form }} (10 vol), add {{ drug.strength }} of dibutyl phthalate and titrate with 0.1M ammonium thiocyanate using ferric ammonium sulphate {{ drug.dosage_form }} as indicator, shaking vigorously after each addition of titrant. Perform a blank determination and make any necessary correction. Each ml of 0.1M silver nitrate is equivalent to 0.{{ drug.strength }} of NaCl.

Sodium glycollate: To 0.{{ drug.strength }} add {{ drug.strength }} of glacial acetic acid, mix well and add {{ drug.strength }} of water, stirring occasionally until {{ drug.dosage_form }} is complete. Slowly add {{ drug.strength }} of acetone with stirring and then add {{ drug.strength }} of sodium chloride. Filter, wash the residue with acetone and dilute the filtrate to {{ drug.strength }} with acetone. Transfer {{ drug.strength }} of this {{ drug.dosage_form }} to an open flask, heat on a water-bath for exactly 20 minutes, cool, add {{ drug.strength }} of naphthalenediol reagent and mix thoroughly. Add a further {{ drug.strength }} of the same reagent, mix, cover the flask with aluminium foil and heat on a water-bath for 20 minutes. Cool and dilute to {{ drug.strength }} with sulphuric acid. The absorbance of the resulting {{ drug.dosage_form }} at the maximum at 540 nm using water as the blank, , is not more than that of a {{ drug.dosage_form }} prepared in the following manner. To {{ drug.strength }} of a 0.062% w/v {{ drug.dosage_form }} of glycollic acid, previously dried at a pressure not exceeding 2 kPa for 16 hours, add {{ drug.strength }} of glacial acetic acid, dilute to {{ drug.strength }} with acetone and complete the procedure described above beginning at the words "Transfer {{ drug.strength }}...." (2.0%).

Microbial limits: 1.{{ drug.strength }} is free from Escherichia coli and salmonellae,

Loss on drying: Not more than 10.0%, determined on 0.{{ drug.strength }} by drying in an oven at 105o,

Assay: Weigh accurately about {{ drug.strength }}, add {{ drug.strength }} of a mixture of 4 volumes of ethanol (95%) and 1 volume of water, add 0.{{ drug.strength }} of phenolphthalein {{ drug.dosage_form }} and mix. Add 1M sodium hydroxide dropwise until the colour of the {{ drug.dosage_form }} becomes faintly pink, shake for 30 minutes and decant through a sintered glass crucible. Repeat the extraction three times, or until a test for chloride ions is negative. Transfer the bulk of the residue to the crucible, wash the residue with ethanol (95%) and dry at 110o to constant weight. Weigh accurately 0.{{ drug.strength }} of the residue, add {{ drug.strength }} of anhydrous glacial acetic acid, heat under a reflux condenser for 2 hours, cool and carry out Method A for non-aqueous titration,  determining the end-point potentiometrically. Each ml of 0.1M perchloric acid is equivalent to 0.{{ drug.strength }} of Na.
